<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Feeble" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Feeble,</orth> weak: <cit><quote>f. age,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 941" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 941</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. luc 1768" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1768</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 7.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 7, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.4.35" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 4, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.3.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 3, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.288" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 288</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.208" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 208</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 130</bibl>. <cit><quote>f. Desire,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 710" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 710</bibl></cit> (== exhausted). <bibl n="shak. pp 319" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 319</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.7.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 7, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.6.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 6, 22</bibl>. <cit><quote>a lady's f. voice,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.41" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 41</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.310" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 310</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.313" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 313</bibl>. <cit><quote>every f. rumour,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.3.125" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 3, 125</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to help the f. up,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 107</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.4.36" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 36</bibl>. Denoting want of military strength: <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 22</bibl>. Mental weakness: <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 1, 2</bibl>. <cit><quote>ere my tongue shall wound my honour with such f. wrong,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.191" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 191</bibl></cit> (with the wrong of such weakness, such cowardice).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>